attributes.background:
The DCMS approved pay remit for the Maritime Museum in 2009 should include the following features:
1. an increase for all staff in post within the upper quartile of the 2009/10 pay remit guidance;
2. this increase to be distributed in an open and transparent manner
3. a pay benchmarking exercise with other National museums in London to ensure pay rates and the total reward package are broadly comparable;
4. a commitment to introduce the London Living Wage
